 323:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
 324:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief Enable GPIO pull-up state in Standby and Shutdown modes.
 325:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Set the relevant PUy bits of PWR_PUCRx register to configure the I/O in
 326:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        pull-up state in Standby and Shutdown modes.
 327:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  This state is effective in Standby and Shutdown modes only if APC bit
 328:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        is set through HAL_PWREx_EnablePullUpPullDownConfig() API.
 329:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  The configuration is lost when exiting the Shutdown mode due to the
 330:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        power-on reset, maintained when exiting the Standby mode.
 331:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  To avoid any conflict at Standby and Shutdown modes exits, the corresponding
 332:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        PDy bit of PWR_PDCRx register is cleared unless it is reserved.
 333:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Even if a PUy bit to set is reserved, the other PUy bits entered as input
 334:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        parameter at the same time are set.
 335:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param GPIO Specify the IO port. This parameter can be PWR_GPIO_A, ..., PWR_GPIO_H
 336:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         to select the GPIO peripheral.
 337:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param GPIONumber Specify the I/O pins numbers.
 338:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         This parameter can be one of the following values:
 339:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         PWR_GPIO_BIT_0, ..., PWR_GPIO_BIT_15 (except for PORTH where less
 340:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         I/O pins are available) or the logical OR of several of them to set
 341:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         several bits for a given port in a single API call.
