 441:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
 442:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief Enable GPIO pull-down state in Standby and Shutdown modes.
 443:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Set the relevant PDy bits of PWR_PDCRx register to configure the I/O in
 444:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        pull-down state in Standby and Shutdown modes.
 445:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  This state is effective in Standby and Shutdown modes only if APC bit
 446:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        is set through HAL_PWREx_EnablePullUpPullDownConfig() API.
 447:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  The configuration is lost when exiting the Shutdown mode due to the
 448:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        power-on reset, maintained when exiting the Standby mode.
 449:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  To avoid any conflict at Standby and Shutdown modes exits, the corresponding
 450:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        PUy bit of PWR_PUCRx register is cleared unless it is reserved.
 451:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Even if a PDy bit to set is reserved, the other PDy bits entered as input
 452:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        parameter at the same time are set.
 453:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param GPIO Specify the IO port. This parameter can be PWR_GPIO_A..PWR_GPIO_H
 454:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         to select the GPIO peripheral.
 455:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param GPIONumber Specify the I/O pins numbers.
 456:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         This parameter can be one of the following values:
 457:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         PWR_GPIO_BIT_0, ..., PWR_GPIO_BIT_15 (except for PORTH where less
 458:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         I/O pins are available) or the logical OR of several of them to set
 459:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         several bits for a given port in a single API call.
 460:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @retval HAL Status
 461:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   */
