1286:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h **** /**
1287:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   * @brief  Disable ExtiLine Falling Edge Trigger for Lines in range 32 to 63
1288:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   * @note The configurable wakeup lines are edge-triggered. No glitch must be
1289:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *       generated on these lines. If a Falling edge on a configurable interrupt
1290:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *       line occurs during a write operation in the EXTI_FTSR register, the
1291:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *       pending bit is not set.
1292:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *       Rising and falling edge triggers can be set for the same interrupt line.
1293:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *       In this case, both generate a trigger condition.
1294:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   * @rmtoll FTSR2        FTx           LL_EXTI_DisableFallingTrig_32_63
1295:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   * @param  ExtiLine This parameter can be a combination of the following values:
1296:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_EXTI_LINE_33 (*)
1297:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_EXTI_LINE_40
1298:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_EXTI_LINE_41
1299:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32wbxx_ll_exti.h ****   *         (*) value not defined in all devices
