1079:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /****************************************************************************/
1080:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1081:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
1082:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief Enter Stop 0 mode.
1083:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 0 mode, main and low voltage regulators are ON.
1084:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 0 mode, all I/O pins keep the same state as in Run mode.
1085:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  All clocks in the VCORE domain are stopped; the PLL, the MSI,
1086:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        the HSI and the HSE oscillators are disabled. Some peripherals with the wakeup capabilit
1087:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        (I2Cx, USARTx and LPUART) can switch on the HSI to receive a frame, and switch off the H
1088:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        after receiving the frame if it is not a wakeup frame. In this case, the HSI clock is pr
1089:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        only to the peripheral requesting it.
1090:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        SRAM1, SRAM2 and register contents are preserved.
1091:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        The BOR is available.
1092:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  When exiting Stop 0 mode by issuing an interrupt or a wakeup event,
1093:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the HSI RC oscillator is selected as system clock if STOPWUCK bit in RCC_CFGR register
1094:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         is set; the MSI oscillator is selected if STOPWUCK is cleared.
1095:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  By keeping the internal regulator ON during Stop 0 mode, the consumption
1096:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         is higher although the startup time is reduced.
1097:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Case of Stop0 mode with SMPS: Before entering Stop 0 mode with SMPS Step Down converter 
1098:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        the HSI16 must be kept on by enabling HSI kernel clock (set HSIKERON register bit).
1099:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  According to system power policy, system entering in Stop mode
1100:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        is depending on other CPU power mode.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Nathan\AppData\Local\Temp\ccfQQZVb.s 			page 117


1101:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param STOPEntry  specifies if Stop mode in entered with WFI or WFE instruction.
1102:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
1103:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFI  Enter Stop mode with WFI instruction
1104:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFE  Enter Stop mode with WFE instruction
1105:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @retval None
1106:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   */
