1137:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
1138:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief Enter Stop 1 mode.
1139:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 1 mode, only low power voltage regulator is ON.
1140:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 1 mode, all I/O pins keep the same state as in Run mode.
1141:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  All clocks in the VCORE domain are stopped; the PLL, the MSI,
1142:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        the HSI and the HSE oscillators are disabled. Some peripherals with the wakeup capabilit
1143:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        (I2Cx, USARTx and LPUART) can switch on the HSI to receive a frame, and switch off the H
1144:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        after receiving the frame if it is not a wakeup frame. In this case, the HSI clock is pr
1145:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        only to the peripheral requesting it.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Nathan\AppData\Local\Temp\ccfQQZVb.s 			page 119


1146:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        SRAM1, SRAM2 and register contents are preserved.
1147:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        The BOR is available.
1148:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  When exiting Stop 1 mode by issuing an interrupt or a wakeup event,
1149:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the HSI RC oscillator is selected as system clock if STOPWUCK bit in RCC_CFGR register
1150:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         is set; the MSI oscillator is selected if STOPWUCK is cleared.
1151:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Due to low power mode, an additional startup delay is incurred when waking up from Stop 
1152:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  According to system power policy, system entering in Stop mode
1153:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        is depending on other CPU power mode.
1154:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param STOPEntry  specifies if Stop mode in entered with WFI or WFE instruction.
1155:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
1156:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFI  Enter Stop mode with WFI instruction
1157:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFE  Enter Stop mode with WFE instruction
1158:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @retval None
1159:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   */
