1190:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
1191:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief Enter Stop 2 mode.
1192:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 2 mode, only low power voltage regulator is ON.
1193:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  In Stop 2 mode, all I/O pins keep the same state as in Run mode.
1194:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  All clocks in the VCORE domain are stopped, the PLL, the MSI,
1195:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        the HSI and the HSE oscillators are disabled. Some peripherals with wakeup capability
1196:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        (LCD, LPTIM1, I2C3 and LPUART) can switch on the HSI to receive a frame, and switch off 
1197:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        receiving the frame if it is not a wakeup frame. In this case the HSI clock is propagate
1198:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        to the peripheral requesting it.
1199:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        SRAM1, SRAM2 and register contents are preserved.
1200:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        The BOR is available.
1201:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        The voltage regulator is set in low-power mode but LPR bit must be cleared to enter stop
1202:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        Otherwise, Stop 1 mode is entered.
1203:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  When exiting Stop 2 mode by issuing an interrupt or a wakeup event,
1204:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the HSI RC oscillator is selected as system clock if STOPWUCK bit in RCC_CFGR register
1205:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         is set; the MSI oscillator is selected if STOPWUCK is cleared.
1206:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  Case of Stop2 mode and debugger probe attached: a workaround should be applied.
1207:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        Issue specified in "ES0394 - STM32WB55Cx/Rx/Vx device errata":
1208:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        2.2.9 Incomplete Stop 2 mode entry after a wakeup from debug upon EXTI line 48 event
1209:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        "With the JTAG debugger enabled on GPIO pins and after a wakeup from debug triggered by 
1210:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        line 48 (CDBGPWRUPREQ), the device may enter in a state in which attempts to enter Stop 
1211:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        effective ..."
1212:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        Workaround implementation example using LL driver:
1213:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        LL_EXTI_DisableIT_32_63(LL_EXTI_LINE_48);
1214:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        LL_C2_EXTI_DisableIT_32_63(LL_EXTI_LINE_48);
1215:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note  According to system power policy, system entering in Stop mode
1216:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *        is depending on other CPU power mode.
1217:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param STOPEntry  specifies if Stop mode in entered with WFI or WFE instruction.
1218:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
1219:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFI  Enter Stop mode with WFI instruction
1220:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *            @arg @ref PWR_STOPENTRY_WFE  Enter Stop mode with WFE instruction
1221:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @retval None
1222:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   */
